postcontent: This is a HUNTING AR with some knock-down power in a 6.8.  It will kill deer and pigs as good as most larger caliber rifles do at close to medium range (250 yards in- where 99% of shots are made by the average hunter).The upper is a 100% factory assembled and tested Yankee Hill Machine (YHM) upper (bought from Midway in 2015) and uses a very sturdy, SMOOTH floating hand-guard without all the excessive holes you get with a four sided rail (that gets DIRTY fast in the field and has sharp edges that hang on everything).  But if you need to hang more gear on your gun, YHM (and others) sell rails to fit the barrel/bolt system used on this upper.  Using a 1-10 twist, 20" chromed YHM-88-F (their fluted diamond etched barrel without end threads), you get a more QUIET barrel with both accuracy and long barrel life from a company with a long, and solid record of performance.  YHM is sold by Midway, Brownells and reputable sellers-- because they provide a good mid-range product with rock solid performance.The lower is a perfectly matched (zero play- locks up perfectly) Palmetto State Armory (PSA) forged lower with a basic trigger upgrade and has mid-range Magpul furniture.  There is a sling ready post on the rear stock and then, behind the receiver... there is also a "clip-on" shoulder strap (two-sided) ring for a tactical (hang down) strap (not included).At 7 1/2 lbs this gun is close to 1/2 the weight of a 308 AR-- and so it is much easier to handle/carry out in the field.  This gun has about 150 rounds through it and is gently used with light wear in a few expected places- no surprises on condition.  I got this rifle for pig hunting, but without another few $k for a thermal scope, I have decided to go back to my bolt guns for the limited night hunting I do.  It is sold without an optic, but for another $150, this rifle can come with a NEW Alpen 3x9 scope, riser and rings- bore sighted.  The Alpen is a fantastic scope (just check it's ratings) with an steel, 6.8 spec magazine).  $900 with the new scope included and bore sighted on a riser /better rings).  I would sell the upper for $550 also as I can keep the lower for a 6.5 grendel (future) project.  Yes you can build a new AR 6.8 for $750, but you won't get a YHM built and tested upper, a premium barrel, or MagPul upgrades without spending closer to $1000 (today).Emails replied to in kind, no shipping please unless I keep the lower, then $15 insured shipping for the upper only (w/o scope).  I prefer a face-to-face meet-up near Emporia, KS or I could meet 1/2 way for some gas money
